{"id":1360,"date":"2021-05-07T17:40:37","date_gmt":"2021-05-07T17:40:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/?p=1360"},"modified":"2021-05-07T17:55:04","modified_gmt":"2021-05-07T17:55:04","slug":"qa-responses-07-05-2021","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/2021\/05\/07\/qa-responses-07-05-2021\/","title":{"rendered":"Q&#038;A Responses (07\/05\/2021)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Thank you for all the questions submitted over the last few weeks &#8211; below are answers straight from the developers on your most pressing and requested questions! As a reminder, support queries and game issues that get submitted in the Q&amp;A form will not be answered or picked up by our Customer Support team. Please direct all support questions through the in-game Help function. If you do not see your submitted question answered in this post, it may have already been answered in a previous Q&amp;A blog, so please check those before re-submitting your queries.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always all information in this post is subject to change.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em><strong><em>When and how are you going to launch the Archmage\u2019s Staff?<\/em><\/strong><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While we have not revealed any details on the Archmage Staff either in-game or through blog posts, we are aware that players are nonetheless eagerly discussing and speculating about this exciting new relic!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore we will take this opportunity to announce and outline some details:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"599\" height=\"651\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/archmage_staff2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1369\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/archmage_staff2.png 599w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/archmage_staff2-276x300.png 276w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>We plan on making this relic available in the Divine Temple next week in <strong>a stand-alone Altar for 8,000 Divine Gems.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em>Collection Relics<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some players may have also seen some new additions to the Collection Relics!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As of right now here are the intended changes &amp; additions made:<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Norse I Collection relic <em>Svallin <\/em>updated<\/li><li>Norse II Collection introduced with brand new relic <em>Rati<\/em><\/li><li>Archmage Collection introduced with brand new relic <em>Tesseract<\/em><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Details and skills on the new relics are featured below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"600\" height=\"594\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/svallin_relic.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1362\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/svallin_relic.png 600w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/svallin_relic-300x297.png 300w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/svallin_relic-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"601\" height=\"595\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/rati.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1363\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/rati.png 601w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/rati-300x297.png 300w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/rati-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 601px) 100vw, 601px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/tesseract.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1364\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/tesseract.png 602w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/tesseract-300x281.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em><strong><em>Why does Frigg not have a synergy with the Norse relics?<\/em><\/strong><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Many players have been right to point out that Frigg despite being a God from Norse mythology does not get any synergy bonuses from <em>Rati <\/em>or <em>Svallin<\/em>!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Rest assured that we have not forgotten about Frigg, even with <em>Skidbladnir <\/em>equipped this <em>War God <\/em>hungers for more power and her Spirit will not rest until she has reached her full potential!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><br><strong><em><strong><em>What exactly is \u2018Spell All Elemental Damage\u2019?<\/em><\/strong><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Spell All Elemental Damage is an effect that is applied when a relic or Titan increases the damage of all spells, regardless of their Element.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>FIreball<\/em> inflicts Fire damage,&nbsp; <em>Poison Cloud<\/em> inflicts Poison Damage , and so on.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If a relic boosts \u201cSpell All Elemental Damage\u201d, it will boost all spells\u2019 damage regardless of their elemental type when using a mixed loadout.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We are going to change the wording for this effect to \u201cAll Spell Damage\u201d in future. Note that <em>Shield<\/em> spells are not affected, since <em>Shield<\/em> spells do not deal damage.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em><strong><em>Can you run another event where we get a choice of Titans as a reward?<\/em><\/strong><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We know the community really engaged with our last \u2018Blade and Bulwark\u2018 style events and we currently have plans to run a similarly structured event like this in the coming weeks!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em><strong><strong><em>Can you update the calendar?<\/em><\/strong><\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A calendar update went live earlier today!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em><strong><em>What relics will be available in Altar Of Abundance next week? Will every Berserker drop too?<\/em><\/strong><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every 4* Berserker (including Hel &amp; Lifespark) will be in the drop pool at equal rates. Below are some of the relics that will be available from the altar:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Berserker signature relics: <\/strong>&nbsp;Egg Of Illuyanka, Bronze Kishar, Heart Of Seri, Anguta\u2019s Grasp, Heart Of Tizheruk, Beowulf\u2019s Spaulder, Heart Of Hwit Draca, Sekhmet\u2019s Aegis, Ancient Rosetta, Bloodied Sickle, Sky Shackles, Tail Of Cerberus, Chains Of Cerberus<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dracones &amp; instruments:<\/strong> Draco Ignis, Draco Glacies, Draco Lapis, Drum Of The Earth, Storm Kymbala, Harp Of Frost, Trumpet Of Iron, Horn Of Infernus, Putrid Pipes, Bell Of Despair<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>All the elemental variants of <strong>Banners, Runes, Vials &amp; Charms <\/strong>and more!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em>Can you explain the third skill of the \u2018Arca\u2019 relics please?&nbsp;<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em>(20 second cooldown mechanic)<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using Arca Lapidum as an example:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"256\" height=\"256\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/Chest_Physical.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1365\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/Chest_Physical.png 256w, https:\/\/blog.dawnoftitans.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/Chest_Physical-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px\" \/><figcaption><strong>Arca Lapidum<\/strong><\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><em>On Allied Troop death, 35% chance to cast Shield on Titan and 3 troops (20 second Cooldown)<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 20 second Cooldown is a unique condition on the Arca relics, and means that the relic\u2019s effect can only occur once within a period of 20 seconds.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>An Allied Troop dies in battle.<\/li><li><em>Arca Lapidum<\/em> chance activates, and Shield is cast on the Titan and 3 troops.<\/li><li><em>Arca Lapidum<\/em> will go on cooldown for 20 seconds,&nbsp; which means that this effect cannot activate again until a 20 second \u201ccooldown period\u201d has passed.<\/li><li>After 20 seconds have passed, Arca Lapidum is re-activated, with a 35% chance to Shield the Titan and 3 Troops.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>In testing all the Arca relics, spreading out the triggers over the course of a battle was beneficial to the overall impact of the relics and made battles more varied.&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Thank you for all the questions submitted over the last few weeks &#8211; below are answers straight from the developers on your most pressing and&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status"